{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Athletics Federation of Guinea-Bissau |abbrev = FAGB |logo = Federação de Atletismo da Guiné-Bissau Logo.png |logosize = 180px |sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|1988}} |aff = [[IAAF]] |affdate = {{Start date|1991}} |region = [[Confederation of African Athletics|CAA]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Bissau]] |location = |president = [[Renato Moura]] |chairman = |chairperson = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |secretary = [[Ukessano Lima]] |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = |countryflag = Guinea-Bissau |countryflag2 = |countryflag3 = |more = }}
The '''Athletics Federation of Guinea-Bissau''' ('''FAGB'''; ''Federação de Atletismo da Guiné-Bissau'') is the governing body for the sport of athletics in [[Guinea-Bissau]]. The current president is [[Renato Moura]].<ref name=iaaf_1> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = Federacao de Atletismo da Guinea-Bissau | url = http://www.iaaf.org/about-iaaf/structure/member-federations/africa#GBS | publisher = [[IAAF]] | page = | language = | accessdate = January 8, 2013 }} </ref><ref name=fagb_1> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = September 25, 2012 | title = Presidente Renato Moura e o Director Técnico da FAGB Adão Camala, nas celebracoes do 39º Aniversario da Independencia da Guiné-Bissau, Bissau 24/09/2012 | url = http://www.facebook.com/FAGuineBissau | publisher = Federação de Atletismo da Guiné-Bissau | page = | language = Portuguese | accessdate = October 22, 2012 }} </ref>
== History == FAGB was founded in 1988,<ref name=aia> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = El Atletismo Iberoamericano | url = http://www.rfea.es/aeea/archivos/libroiberoamericano2010.pdf | publisher = [[Real Federación Española de Atletismo]] | page = 20 | language = Spanish | accessdate = October 22, 2012 }} </ref> and was affiliated to the [[IAAF]] in the year 1991.<ref name=iaaf_2> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = | title = ASOCIACIÓN INTERNACIONAL DE FEDERACIONES DE ATLETISMO - CONSTITUCIÓN EN VIGOR A PARTIR DEL 1 DE NOVIEMBRE DE 2011 | url = http://www.iaaf.org/mm/Document/06/28/25/62825_PDF_Spanish.pdf | publisher = [[IAAF]] | page = 58 | language = Spanish | accessdate = October 22, 2012 }} </ref>
== Affiliations == *[[International Association of Athletics Federations]] (IAAF) *[[Confederation of African Athletics]] (CAA) *[[Asociación Iberoamericana de Atletismo]] (AIA; ''Ibero-American Athletics Association'') Moreover, it is part of the following national organisations: *[[Guinea-Bissau Olympic Committee]] (Portuguese: ''Comité Olímpico da Guiné-Bissau'')
== National records == FAGB maintains the [[List of Bissau-Guinean records in athletics|national records]].
