'''Orna Datz''' ( {{lang-he|אורנה דץ}}; born '''Orna Cohen''' born 10 May 1964) is an [[Israel]]i singer, actress and television presenter.

==Biography==
Orna Cohen was born in Holon, Israel, to a Jewish family. At age 17, she was elected "Miss Holon". In 1987 she married the singer [[Moshe Datz]] and they became known as the [[Duo Datz]]. In 2001 she began to host the fashion tv series ''Makeover'' (מהפך) [http://www.haaretz.com/the-thrall-of-the-new-1.73083], and in 2006 she began hosting the Israeli version of ''[[The Swan (TV series)|The Swan]]''. In 2005 and 2006 she presented the [[Miss Israel]] Beauty pageant [http://bidur.nana10.co.il/Article/?ArticleID=178432].

