{{Notability|date=December 2017}}
'''Peter Froggatt''' (born 29 December 1934, [[Glossop, Derbyshire]]) is a British talent agent. He attended Hyde Grammar School before training at The [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]] in [[London]].

He founded one of Great Britain's top [[theatrical]] agencies, Plant & Froggatt in 1965.<ref name="stage">{{cite book|title=The Stage Year Book|date=1969|page=255|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=XEvWAAAAMAAJ&q=%22peter+froggatt%22+agent&dq=%22peter+froggatt%22+agent&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjckdShxvTZAhUBPsAKHRkqDP4Q6AEIODAD|accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref> It became Markham & Froggatt, and later  Markham Froggatt and Irwin,<ref name="markham">{{cite web|title=Pippa Markham|url=http://www.bafta.org/about/key-personnel/film-committee|website=Film Committee|publisher=BAFTA|accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref><ref name="mfi">{{cite web|title=Home page|url=http://www.markhamfroggattandirwin.com/|publisher=Markham Froggatt & Irwin|accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref> and is still in the top ten of talent agents. He is now retired in the [[Cotswolds]].{{Cn|date=December 2017}}

