'''''Sleeping Queens''''' is a children's [[card game]] manufactured by Gamewright. The game was invented by six-year-old Miranda Evarts.<ref>{{cite news | last =Grant | first =Tracy | coauthors = | title =Chance to Dream; Sleepless Young Inventor Plays Her Cards Right | work =Style | pages =C13 | language = | publisher =The Washington Post | date =2005-03-15 | url =http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2005/mar/15/sleepless_young_inventor/ | accessdate =2007-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last= |first= |coauthors= |title=Miranda Is the Queen of Cards |work=Time For Kids |pages=Vol. 10, No. 23 |language= |publisher=Time Magazine |date=2005-04-08 |url=http://www.timeforkids.com/TFK/magazines/story/0,6277,1045055,00.html |accessdate=2007-02-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927212620/http://www.timeforkids.com/TFK/magazines/story/0,6277,1045055,00.html |archivedate=September 27, 2007 }}</ref>
Miranda's family helped her develop the game and find a [[publishing|publisher]]. Sleeping Queens has received praise, including being chosen by the Canadian Toy Testing Council as one of its "2006 Best Bet Awards" selections.<ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =2006 Best Bet Awards | work = | publisher =Canadian Toy Testing Council | year =2006 | url =http://www.toy-testing.org/content/BestBets/bb06.htm | doi = | accessdate = 2007-02-04 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061126221433/http://www.toy-testing.org/content/BestBets/bb06.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2006-11-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last =McPherson | first =Karen | coauthors = | title =Summer's hot toys keep kids active and creative | work =Lifestyle | pages = | language = | publisher =[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]] | date =2005-04-08 | url =http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/05144/509208.stm | accessdate =2007-02-04}}</ref>
